1
00:01:00,290 --> 00:01:02,046
Thanks so much, Oppa.

2
00:01:02,070 --> 00:01:04,390
Thanks to you, I could.

3
00:01:30,260 --> 00:01:31,896
It's you, isn't it?

4
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:34,376
Yeong Rye's friend from back then.

5
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,296
Your name was Seo...

6
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,546
Seo Jong Hui.

7
00:01:37,570 --> 00:01:39,786
That's right. Jong Hui.

8
00:01:39,810 --> 00:01:42,726
What are the odds we
run into each other here?

9
00:01:42,750 --> 00:01:44,720
It's really good to see you.

10
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:05,266
Are you okay?

11
00:02:05,290 --> 00:02:09,676
If you fell off the horse,
you should get checked out

12
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:12,500
- like Jae Pil said.
- I'm fine.

13
00:02:13,190 --> 00:02:15,800
It's just a simple bruise.

14
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:20,786
Worry about stopping your hiccups first.

15
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:23,610
Try holding your breath.

16
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:28,676
Here. Drink this.

17
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:30,146
Let's stop those hiccups.

18
00:02:30,170 --> 00:02:31,850
Thank you.

19
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,680
Give it to me. I'll open it for you.

20
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:09,706
I think they're gone now.

21
00:03:09,730 --> 00:03:11,736
Good.

22
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:14,596
It's been a while since I've seen
the three of you together.

23
00:03:14,620 --> 00:03:17,496
Seven years ago at
the police station, right?

24
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,916
You were so fresh back then.

25
00:03:19,940 --> 00:03:21,166
Now, we're getting old together.

26
00:03:21,190 --> 00:03:23,266
You two are both ladies now.

27
00:03:23,290 --> 00:03:26,546
You're the only one who
hasn't changed, Hyungnim.

28
00:03:26,570 --> 00:03:29,886
You're still so cheerful,
both then and now.

29
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:33,736
Is that so? That doesn't
sound like a compliment.

30
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:36,050
Is it my inferiority complex?

31
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:44,276
- Jong Hui.
- Mom!

32
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:47,696
Are you okay? You're okay, right?

33
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:50,820
Yes. I'm fine.

34
00:03:51,770 --> 00:03:54,966
When Mr. Jeong told me,
my heart was pounding so hard.

35
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:57,600
I don't even know how I got here.

36
00:03:59,050 --> 00:04:01,106
Gosh, Jong Hui.

37
00:04:01,130 --> 00:04:04,106
Mom, I'm okay.

38
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:06,646
I'm perfectly fine.

39
00:04:06,670 --> 00:04:09,490
- P-Please calm down.
- Yes...

40
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:14,306
Gosh, this is so upsetting.

41
00:04:14,330 --> 00:04:17,200
I really don't need to be hospitalized.

42
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:20,646
I'm so fine that it's almost
embarrassing, Mom.

43
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:23,086
There's nothing to be embarrassed about.

44
00:04:23,110 --> 00:04:25,696
Just think of it as taking a few days off.

45
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:28,556
I've been meaning to get you
a proper checkup anyway.

46
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:31,446
But I've been so busy
that I've neglected it.

47
00:04:31,470 --> 00:04:34,600
Even my Seung Yeon used
to go at least once a year...

48
00:04:38,390 --> 00:04:42,306
Anyway, let's get you
checked this time, okay?

49
00:04:42,330 --> 00:04:43,750
Okay.

50
00:04:53,410 --> 00:04:58,796
A few days ago, Jong Hui came to our salon.

51
00:04:58,820 --> 00:05:01,766
With her adoptive mother.

52
00:05:01,790 --> 00:05:03,776
Oh, is that so?

53
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:08,126
I was going to tell you,
but I missed the right moment.

54
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:12,610
Really. When I came by to drop off
your clothes that time…

55
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:15,256
It's fine.

56
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:18,280
You don't have to explain
yourself. Why would you?

57
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:23,676
Are you really okay?

58
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:26,286
You must've been very shocked.

59
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:28,046
A bit.

60
00:05:28,070 --> 00:05:31,660
For a few seconds, I wasn't
sure what I was seeing.

61
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:35,326
Isn't that just so like her?

62
00:05:35,350 --> 00:05:37,766
Vanishing like the wind

63
00:05:37,790 --> 00:05:40,470
and then showing up again suddenly.

64
00:05:41,790 --> 00:05:44,670
Right. Just like Seo Jong Hui.

65
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:49,016
Here comes the bus.

66
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:51,446
I'm going. You head in.

67
00:05:51,470 --> 00:05:53,640
- Bye.
- Get home safe.

68
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:00,100
Go.

69
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,840
Bye.

70
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,590
Any dizziness or nausea?

71
00:06:29,370 --> 00:06:30,850
No.

72
00:06:31,650 --> 00:06:33,676
As you probably know,
at your guardian's request,

73
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,726
we'll be running a series of tests.

74
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:37,406
It's too late today,

75
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:41,426
so we'll likely start
early tomorrow morning.

76
00:06:41,450 --> 00:06:42,800
Okay.

77
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:49,766
Your needle phobia has
been noted, so don't worry.

78
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:53,636
If you're uncomfortable even
a little bit, call the nurse.

79
00:06:53,660 --> 00:06:55,806
Do you have any questions?

80
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:57,720
Yes, I do.

81
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,360
Have you been well?

82
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,840
Yes.

83
00:07:11,790 --> 00:07:13,256
As you can see.

84
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:17,170
I heard from Yeong Rye
that you became a doctor.

85
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,826
But wow.

86
00:07:19,850 --> 00:07:24,380
Seeing you in a white coat
like this is kind of unfamiliar.

87
00:07:25,460 --> 00:07:27,936
In my memory, you're still

88
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:32,226
wearing a school uniform or
boxing gloves. That's about it.

89
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:34,840
Looks like you studied hard.

90
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,870
It was the only thing I could do.

91
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,840
But how did you end up.

92
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:53,836
I'll take your blood pressure, ma'am.

93
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:55,250
Sure.

94
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,160
Hey.

95
00:08:21,970 --> 00:08:25,616
If you wanted to drink, we should've
gone to a pub or a food stall.

96
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:28,796
I feel awkward in a place like this.

97
00:08:28,820 --> 00:08:30,806
If I buy you a drink here
after you become a judge,

98
00:08:30,830 --> 00:08:32,666
it might look shady.

99
00:08:32,690 --> 00:08:34,356
So, I'm buying in advance.

100
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:36,500
Drink as much as you want.

101
00:08:45,590 --> 00:08:48,636
What's up? Is something going on?

102
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:51,130
Something is going on.

103
00:08:55,550 --> 00:09:00,740
I just feel like things are
about to get interesting.

104
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:04,346
You know that tension.

105
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:09,486
Like the strange flutter before a storm.

106
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:12,956
The sky is heavy with black clouds

107
00:09:12,980 --> 00:09:15,296
and the wind whipping around.

108
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,276
It hasn't started raining yet,

109
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:21,636
but the sky turns grand and ominous,
like it could pour any second.

110
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:25,110
Just say it so I can understand. Be direct.

111
00:09:27,470 --> 00:09:31,096
You have no sense of literary refinement.

112
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:33,876
What do you know besides the law?

113
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:36,716
I'm busy reading the law books.
When would I read that stuff?

114
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:39,876
Law school counts as h-humanities,
you knucklehead.

115
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:44,066
Read some books. I can't
communicate with you. Geez...

116
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:47,300
Who do you mean by "The
calm before the storm"?

117
00:09:48,490 --> 00:09:50,060
Who knows?

118
00:09:52,070 --> 00:09:55,956
Yeong Rye. Jae Pil. Jong Hui.

119
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:59,580
And maybe also us?

120
00:10:21,150 --> 00:10:23,866
Out of people who brushed past my life,

121
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:26,336
I used to think those
who left are mere ties

122
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:30,290
and the ones who stayed are destiny.

123
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:35,266
Then, as for the one who returns,

124
00:10:35,290 --> 00:10:39,616
is she a mere connection or destiny?

125
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:43,660
Or just a coincidence?

126
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:23,010
[Episode 9: A Connection Lost]

127
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:29,416
[vs. A Destiny Kept]

128
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:33,680
[Yeonseo University Hospital]

129
00:11:49,460 --> 00:11:52,220
Why don't you eat some more?

130
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:57,556
Should I take it outside?

131
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,876
Yes.

132
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:03,050
This is for patients, but I'm
not a patient. I have no appetite.

133
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:17,010
[VIP Ward]

134
00:12:18,930 --> 00:12:21,606
But still, this is such a waste.

135
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:23,986
What will she do with
no appetite like that?

136
00:12:24,010 --> 00:12:26,420
What a waste.

137
00:12:29,220 --> 00:12:32,360
[VIP Room (1-person suite)]

138
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:35,776
Hey, let's hurry and grab lunch.

139
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:39,000
- I skipped breakfast, and I'm starving.
- Okay.

140
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:43,326
Oh, my, what on earth!

141
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:46,566
The great Ko Yeong Rye
slept through her alarm?

142
00:12:46,590 --> 00:12:48,546
I relied on you and slept like a log.

143
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:52,806
What are we going to do?
At this rate, we're definitely late.

144
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:56,660
Sorry. I was up studying
and fell asleep at dawn.

145
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:00,780
Yeong Rye, get in.

146
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,716
Oppa...

147
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:05,180
Get in.

148
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:13,616
Were you really just passing by?

149
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:15,576
It doesn't seem like it.

150
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,976
You've become so distrustful,
while I haven't seen you.

151
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,686
Believe me. I was just
driving by and thought,

152
00:13:21,710 --> 00:13:23,766
"Isn't that Ko Yeong
Rye? What a coincidence."

153
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:26,016
So I pulled over.

154
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:29,926
Oppa, say something that
makes sense. How could you...

155
00:13:29,950 --> 00:13:33,466
If he says so, then that's how it is.

156
00:13:33,490 --> 00:13:35,176
Why are you grilling him?

157
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:38,776
We were about to be late,
but he showed up like a savior.

158
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,506
I'm so grateful I could cry.

159
00:13:40,530 --> 00:13:44,180
Exactly. I knew I could
count on you, Jeong Bun.

160
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:48,476
What is this? Why are
you two in perfect sync?

161
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:51,466
You said riding in my car felt like flying

162
00:13:51,490 --> 00:13:54,146
compared to riding the packed bus.

163
00:13:54,170 --> 00:13:57,226
I'm playing chauffeur before
I officially start work, Ugly.

164
00:13:57,250 --> 00:14:01,316
Oppa, that was just a figure of speech.

165
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:03,756
I wasn't asking you to drive me to work.

166
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:05,256
I know, silly.

167
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:09,000
Geez, I'm doing this because I want to.

168
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:12,346
I love driving.

169
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:15,336
I love a good morning spin.

170
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:17,136
With two beauties in my car first thing?

171
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,866
What's not to love?

172
00:14:18,890 --> 00:14:21,396
Oh, my. Maybe it's all that
time you spent overseas,

173
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:24,446
but you sure talk sweet as honey.

174
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:26,546
Real nice on the ears.

175
00:14:26,570 --> 00:14:28,360
It's nothing.

176
00:14:34,860 --> 00:14:36,800
Thank you.

177
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,986
Thank you.

178
00:14:41,010 --> 00:14:42,770
Thank you.

179
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:50,230
Thank you.

180
00:14:57,020 --> 00:15:01,840
Ma'am, can I get one pork cutlet to-go?

181
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:08,640
It seemed like you skipped breakfast.

182
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:12,696
The remaining test results can change
depending on whether you've fasted.

183
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,950
Even if you don't feel like it,
it's better to eat a little.

184
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:21,210
W-Wait! Hold on.

185
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:27,190
Could you stay with me while I eat?

186
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:30,530
I don't want to eat alone.

187
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:50,100
What?

188
00:15:51,010 --> 00:15:52,480
Nothing.

189
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:56,086
Just remembered the old days.

190
00:15:56,110 --> 00:15:57,926
You seemed so different,

191
00:15:57,950 --> 00:16:00,390
but you eat pork cutlet the same way.

192
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,370
Right.

193
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:08,746
My mom doesn't like it, so I usually don't.

194
00:16:08,770 --> 00:16:12,566
But with you here, I guess
my old habit slipped out.

195
00:16:12,590 --> 00:16:15,220
But it does taste better this way.

196
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,990
Back then

197
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,350
it was a shock in a good way.

198
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:28,420
Want to hear a secret?

199
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:34,246
That day... I was actually super nervous.

200
00:16:34,270 --> 00:16:37,516
I'd never been to a
Western restaurant before.

201
00:16:37,540 --> 00:16:40,650
I tried so hard not to let it show.

202
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,600
- Really?
- Yeah.

203
00:16:47,620 --> 00:16:50,000
I couldn't tell at all.

204
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:54,630
You were so confident, Seo Jong Hui.

205
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:03,486
Now, you seem like the Han Jae Pil I know.

206
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:05,710
When you smile like that.

207
00:17:08,940 --> 00:17:12,066
And you seem more like
the Seo Jong Hui I know.

208
00:17:12,090 --> 00:17:13,560
Really?

209
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:17,266
Have I really changed that much?

210
00:17:17,290 --> 00:17:19,440
I can't really tell.

211
00:17:27,010 --> 00:17:29,480
I've been wondering about this.

212
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:37,020
I've always wanted to ask you
this if I ever ran into you.

213
00:17:40,450 --> 00:17:44,630
Why did you suddenly tell me we should

214
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,770
stop seeing each other?

215
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:53,370
After that, I went to Vivaldi

216
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:57,586
and found the note you left.

217
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:01,210
And I ran to Cheongah Transportation,
but you were already gone.

218
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:06,840
Why did you do that?

219
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:16,680
I don't know.

220
00:18:18,410 --> 00:18:21,726
I can't really remember.

221
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:24,210
Too much time has passed.

222
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:28,060
You know how fickle I am.

223
00:18:38,930 --> 00:18:40,890
What about you?

224
00:18:42,130 --> 00:18:44,056
You seem awfully close to Yeong Rye.

225
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:46,326
Well, yeah.

226
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:50,576
She's a friend I can't live without now.
As dear as Sang Cheol.

227
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:54,920
Just a close friend?

228
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,100
Huh?

229
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:00,510
Never mind. It's nothing.

230
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:10,106
This is so delicious.

231
00:19:10,130 --> 00:19:12,316
You want a bite?

232
00:19:12,340 --> 00:19:13,960
You can eat it.

233
00:19:27,650 --> 00:19:29,426
No, he's just not here.

234
00:19:29,450 --> 00:19:32,500
My dad was never here from the beginning.

235
00:19:34,460 --> 00:19:37,786
Gosh. Choi Jeong Bun, that fool.

236
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:41,496
She should've found a good man
and lived happily ever after.

237
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:45,136
Why did she have a baby
alone without a father?

238
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:49,006
Gosh, it's really weighing on me.

239
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:54,050
I was going to pick up girls while
Seo Jong Hui was in the hospital.

240
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:59,760
[Jullee Beauty Salon]

241
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,890
Ta-da! Surprise!

242
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:31,576
Jong Hui, how did you

243
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,156
I escaped from the hospital.

244
00:20:33,180 --> 00:20:36,186
It was no big deal,
but it sure was thrilling.

245
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:37,746
My heart is still pounding right now.

246
00:20:37,770 --> 00:20:41,286
Hey. You scared me.

247
00:20:41,310 --> 00:20:42,596
You're really...

248
00:20:42,620 --> 00:20:46,140
Did I scare you? Should I
surprise you even more?

249
00:20:49,470 --> 00:20:51,330
Ta-da!

250
00:20:53,870 --> 00:20:55,990
Han Jae Pil?

251
00:21:01,950 --> 00:21:04,850
I'm here, too, Ko Yeong Rye.

252
00:21:24,910 --> 00:21:26,940
This is so good!

253
00:21:27,460 --> 00:21:29,706
My queasy stomach completely cleared up.

254
00:21:29,730 --> 00:21:30,846
- Good, huh?
- Yeah.

255
00:21:30,870 --> 00:21:32,996
I found this place two years ago.

256
00:21:33,020 --> 00:21:35,616
Ho Suk and Jeong Bun love their tteokbokki.

257
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,686
We even call it "tonic tteokbokki"

258
00:21:37,710 --> 00:21:39,676
because it even cures the common cold.

259
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:42,870
Exactly. If it tastes good, that's a tonic.

260
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:48,326
Jae Pil, why aren't you eating?

261
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:49,926
You skipped dinner, too.

262
00:21:49,950 --> 00:21:53,940
Jae Pil was never good with spicy food.

263
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:56,856
You can't?

264
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,356
Was he like that?

265
00:21:58,380 --> 00:22:00,656
He just didn't show it back then.

266
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,980
Macho pride and all.

267
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:05,290
Hey, hey.

268
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,956
I can't? As if.

269
00:22:07,980 --> 00:22:09,866
I just don't prefer it.

270
00:22:09,890 --> 00:22:12,720
I can eat this whole thing.

271
00:22:15,230 --> 00:22:16,556
Come on, let's eat.

272
00:22:16,580 --> 00:22:18,470
I'm eating.

273
00:22:21,550 --> 00:22:24,590
Hey, hey, d-don't.

274
00:22:25,870 --> 00:22:27,630
I'm eating.

275
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:41,306
Wow!

276
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:43,476
That's good.

277
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:44,616
This place is good.

278
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:47,326
You want some more? Want more?

279
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:49,356
Ma'am, one more plate, please.

280
00:22:49,380 --> 00:22:50,910
Okay!

281
00:22:51,530 --> 00:22:52,916
Wow.

282
00:22:52,940 --> 00:22:54,756
Hey, are you sure you're okay?

283
00:22:54,780 --> 00:22:57,086
Their sauce is spicier
than that of other places.

284
00:22:57,110 --> 00:22:58,666
Yeah, I'm fine.

285
00:22:58,690 --> 00:23:05,150
I don't understand how
I couldn't handle it back then.

286
00:23:06,710 --> 00:23:08,006
Have some, Yeong Rye.

287
00:23:08,030 --> 00:23:10,306
To eat another plate,
we have to clear this one.

288
00:23:10,330 --> 00:23:11,490
Sure.

289
00:23:12,180 --> 00:23:14,560
Rice cakes.

290
00:23:26,190 --> 00:23:28,326
Hey, hey! Are you okay?

291
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:30,340
Here, have some water.

292
00:23:40,610 --> 00:23:42,230
Hi.

293
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:48,426
You're Jeong Bun's daughter, right?

294
00:23:48,450 --> 00:23:51,176
Your name is...

295
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:53,470
Su Jin, right?

296
00:23:55,490 --> 00:23:57,860
Su Jin, let's have some snacks.

297
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:01,106
Oh! Oh, my!

298
00:24:01,130 --> 00:24:02,736
Oh!

299
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:05,176
You're from Cheongah Transportation, right?

300
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:06,646
- Oh, yes!
- Right?

301
00:24:06,670 --> 00:24:09,936
Ms. Im! Im Ho Suk! Right?

302
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:11,246
That's right.

303
00:24:11,270 --> 00:24:12,976
- Yes, I am!
- You look the same.

304
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:16,696
Oh, my goodness. What a small world.

305
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:19,196
Can't believe I'm running
into you here, of all places.

306
00:24:19,220 --> 00:24:21,236
I know. I know!

307
00:24:21,260 --> 00:24:23,846
It's so good to see you.
You haven't changed.

308
00:24:23,870 --> 00:24:25,136
Have you eaten yet?

309
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,286
I'll ask Mother to whip
something up for you.

310
00:24:27,310 --> 00:24:29,610
- Give me a minute.
- Oh, okay.

311
00:24:30,730 --> 00:24:33,470
Gosh, she's the same.

312
00:24:34,770 --> 00:24:37,740
What's that? A rainbow?

313
00:24:38,980 --> 00:24:40,746
You're good at drawing.

314
00:24:40,770 --> 00:24:44,460
You look so pretty, just like your mom.

315
00:24:45,340 --> 00:24:47,140
Let's see.

316
00:24:49,140 --> 00:24:50,730
Do you like money?

317
00:24:56,590 --> 00:24:58,270
Buy some snacks.

318
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,316
It's okay.

319
00:25:00,340 --> 00:25:04,306
Just think of me as one
of your mom's friends.

320
00:25:04,330 --> 00:25:06,070
You can take it.

321
00:25:10,990 --> 00:25:12,856
Why did you come back here?

322
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:16,636
How many times did I tell you
not to come back here?

323
00:25:16,660 --> 00:25:18,996
And why would you give her money?

324
00:25:19,020 --> 00:25:20,636
You think we're beggars? Huh?

325
00:25:20,660 --> 00:25:24,096
No, not at all. She's just so cute.

326
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:28,016
Listen to that nonsense
coming out of your mouth.

327
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:29,636
Get out. Now.

328
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:33,126
We're not serving you
food, so go somewhere else!

329
00:25:33,150 --> 00:25:35,146
Why are you so mad?

330
00:25:35,170 --> 00:25:37,626
Go. Are you deaf?

331
00:25:37,650 --> 00:25:39,346
- Get out!
- What do you mean?

332
00:25:39,370 --> 00:25:41,616
- Shut up and go.
- Why.

333
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:43,250
Seriously.

334
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:46,396
What...

335
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:48,796
What's the problem?

336
00:25:48,820 --> 00:25:51,056
Wait. Let go of me.

337
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:52,676
What's your problem?

338
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:53,926
You're being too harsh.

339
00:25:53,950 --> 00:25:55,716
Am I? How so?

340
00:25:55,740 --> 00:25:57,276
Do you really need to go this far?

341
00:25:57,300 --> 00:26:00,696
I was happy to see you, and I guess

342
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:02,796
I felt bad, too. That's why I came.

343
00:26:02,820 --> 00:26:05,766
Is giving your daughter some money
something to get so mad about?

344
00:26:05,790 --> 00:26:08,266
There you go, making
another freaking speech.

345
00:26:08,290 --> 00:26:10,326
Who are you to give my daughter money?

346
00:26:10,350 --> 00:26:12,476
To my daughter!

347
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:18,116
I'll only say this one more time,

348
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:19,916
so listen carefully, okay?

349
00:26:19,940 --> 00:26:21,946
Don't ever show your face here again.

350
00:26:21,970 --> 00:26:25,266
Because no one here welcomes you, got it?

351
00:26:25,290 --> 00:26:29,376
Wait, why are you treating me like this?

352
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:31,976
- Are you thick in the head?
- Thick?

353
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:35,236
It hasn't even been ten seconds
since I said I won't repeat myself.

354
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:37,706
It's been seven years already.

355
00:26:37,730 --> 00:26:39,106
Must you do this?

356
00:26:39,130 --> 00:26:43,456
To be frank, you're the one
who told me off and left me.

357
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:45,466
I told you off?

358
00:26:45,490 --> 00:26:49,440
You still don't even know
why I did that back then.

359
00:26:50,370 --> 00:26:52,506
I won't waste my breath.

360
00:26:52,530 --> 00:26:54,526
Let go of me.

361
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:55,646
Let go of me!

362
00:26:55,670 --> 00:26:58,016
- So, tell me. Why did you?
- Let go.

363
00:26:58,040 --> 00:26:59,990
Why did you do that?

364
00:27:00,690 --> 00:27:02,666
Can't you hear her?

365
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:04,500
She said to let go.

366
00:27:05,570 --> 00:27:07,056
What the hell?

367
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,876
Who are you to meddle in our business?

368
00:27:09,900 --> 00:27:11,240
Me?

369
00:27:13,740 --> 00:27:16,440
I'm her boyfriend. Now what?

370
00:27:38,130 --> 00:27:40,436
Why did you say that earlier?

371
00:27:40,460 --> 00:27:43,280
How are you my boyfriend?

372
00:27:45,370 --> 00:27:47,566
Say something.

373
00:27:47,590 --> 00:27:50,486
I knew your nosiness
was as big as Mt. Everest,

374
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:53,906
but how could you go
chirping nonsense like that?

375
00:27:53,930 --> 00:27:56,290
What if people get the wrong idea?

376
00:27:58,530 --> 00:28:02,200
That man is Su Jin's father, isn't he?

377
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:12,200
But you don't want him
to lurk around you two.

378
00:28:13,470 --> 00:28:14,940
So.

379
00:28:15,700 --> 00:28:17,560
Use me.

380
00:28:43,190 --> 00:28:45,606
Is it really that funny?

381
00:28:45,630 --> 00:28:47,486
Why not? It's hilarious.

382
00:28:47,510 --> 00:28:50,146
What's so embarrassing
about not handling spicy food?

383
00:28:50,170 --> 00:28:52,826
But you kept forcing it down.

384
00:28:52,850 --> 00:28:56,116
I thought he was going to drain
all the water from the restaurant.

385
00:28:56,140 --> 00:29:00,406
Your belly is sloshing
with water right now, isn't it?

386
00:29:00,430 --> 00:29:02,806
You're so hilarious.

387
00:29:02,830 --> 00:29:04,726
Fine, laugh.

388
00:29:04,750 --> 00:29:07,326
If my sacrifice brings you joy,

389
00:29:07,350 --> 00:29:10,070
I'll gladly sacrifice myself. Laugh it up.

390
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,776
Hey, wait.

391
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:16,476
Let me do that to help the food go down.

392
00:29:16,500 --> 00:29:18,966
Oh, they had this around?

393
00:29:18,990 --> 00:29:22,556
Go ahead. You used to box back then.

394
00:29:22,580 --> 00:29:26,006
Hey, but will you be okay?

395
00:29:26,030 --> 00:29:27,786
Since you started your internship,

396
00:29:27,810 --> 00:29:30,796
you hardly box anymore
in case you hurt your hands.

397
00:29:30,820 --> 00:29:32,850
This much is fine.

398
00:29:49,370 --> 00:29:50,836
Was something there?

399
00:29:50,860 --> 00:29:53,576
I just missed a step.

400
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:56,746
Hey. Come on, Han Jae Pil.

401
00:29:56,770 --> 00:29:58,186
Yeong Rye, you give it a try.

402
00:29:58,210 --> 00:30:00,000
- M-Me?
- Yeah.

403
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:02,860
I'll hold that.

404
00:30:06,620 --> 00:30:08,326
No need to try so hard.

405
00:30:08,350 --> 00:30:09,966
It won't make a difference.

406
00:30:09,990 --> 00:30:11,026
Let her be.

407
00:30:11,050 --> 00:30:13,546
Don't you know Ko Yeong Rye always
gives everything she's got?

408
00:30:13,570 --> 00:30:15,876
- Here I go.
- Okay.

409
00:30:15,900 --> 00:30:17,930
One, two...

410
00:30:23,670 --> 00:30:25,316
- Whoa!
- Whoa.

411
00:30:25,340 --> 00:30:27,946
I won! I won!

412
00:30:27,970 --> 00:30:29,966
I won!

413
00:30:29,990 --> 00:30:32,026
I won...

414
00:30:32,050 --> 00:30:33,816
If I hadn't missed a step.

415
00:30:33,840 --> 00:30:36,770
Do it right, Han Jae Pil.

416
00:30:37,460 --> 00:30:39,496
His pride is totally bruised right now.

417
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,220
Exactly.

418
00:30:42,150 --> 00:30:43,626
What are you doing on your day off?

419
00:30:43,650 --> 00:30:45,226
Let's hang out after I'm discharged.

420
00:30:45,250 --> 00:30:46,336
- Should we?
- Yeah.

421
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:49,206
Okay. I've got so many things
I want to do with you.

422
00:30:49,230 --> 00:30:50,890
Really?

423
00:30:56,310 --> 00:30:58,436
I said it's okay. I don't need a gift.

424
00:30:58,460 --> 00:31:02,600
My mom says your underwear
should be prettier than your outerwear.

425
00:31:03,460 --> 00:31:04,766
How's this?

426
00:31:04,790 --> 00:31:06,006
This one's pretty, too.

427
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:08,466
I really don't need one.

428
00:31:08,490 --> 00:31:10,566
Then, you pick something as well.
I'll get you one, too.

429
00:31:10,590 --> 00:31:12,086
Really?

430
00:31:12,110 --> 00:31:14,370
Then, I'll get...

431
00:31:17,870 --> 00:31:19,726
How's this? Do I look sexy?

432
00:31:19,750 --> 00:31:21,016
It's pretty.

433
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:23,536
Even Madame Aema would be put to shame.

434
00:31:23,560 --> 00:31:25,470
Then, I'll get this one.

435
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:35,116
Oh, my! You're here?

436
00:31:35,140 --> 00:31:37,336
- Just a blowout today, right?
- Yes.

437
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:40,010
- Right this way.
- Please have a seat here.

438
00:31:43,700 --> 00:31:46,216
Did you wear my gift?

439
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:48,056
Yeah, I did.

440
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:50,106
Look.

441
00:31:50,130 --> 00:31:52,016
Should I show you, too?

442
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:55,376
- Hey!
- Jong Hui.

443
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:58,176
- Is everything all right?
- Yes.

444
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:01,536
Please let me know if you need anything.

445
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:03,280
Sure.

446
00:32:08,300 --> 00:32:11,020
Hey, you can't do that!

447
00:32:13,210 --> 00:32:14,990
Stop it.

448
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,956
- I'm back...
- I'll be right back.

449
00:32:19,980 --> 00:32:21,176
You're here?

450
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:23,590
- Unni!
- Come on!

451
00:32:25,660 --> 00:32:28,006
Hey, I dreamed of poop last night.

452
00:32:28,030 --> 00:32:30,056
No wonder we've got
three big parties today.

453
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,896
Wash your hands and help out.

454
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:34,446
When we're done, I'll grill pork belly
and grease your bellies.

455
00:32:34,470 --> 00:32:36,390
Pork belly?

456
00:32:40,980 --> 00:32:44,560
Mother, there's rice out front.
Should I bring it in?

457
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:50,716
Jae Pil did tell me.

458
00:32:50,740 --> 00:32:53,306
I finally get to see you... ma'am.

459
00:32:53,330 --> 00:32:57,046
Come on. What's with the honorifics?

460
00:32:57,070 --> 00:32:59,116
How've you been, Ma Sang Cheol?

461
00:32:59,140 --> 00:33:01,990
- Is it good?
- Yes.

462
00:33:06,820 --> 00:33:08,726
Mom! This is so good.

463
00:33:08,750 --> 00:33:10,316
This is so good.

464
00:33:10,340 --> 00:33:12,836
What kind of magic did
you work on the pork belly?

465
00:33:12,860 --> 00:33:16,556
Oh, hush. Save the lip service
for when you're selling jeotgal.

466
00:33:16,580 --> 00:33:19,136
Eat up. I'll keep grilling.

467
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,790
- Okay!
- Okay.

468
00:33:32,140 --> 00:33:34,056
Jong Hui, eat plenty.

469
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:35,696
All right. It's delicious.

470
00:33:35,720 --> 00:33:38,226
Here, Mom...

471
00:33:38,250 --> 00:33:39,756
Have some while you grill.

472
00:33:39,780 --> 00:33:41,796
It's okay. You eat it.

473
00:33:41,820 --> 00:33:43,776
I'm sick of the smell. I don't want any.

474
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:45,536
It'll go down once you swallow.

475
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:48,180
- Here, open wide.
- I said I don't.

476
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:53,446
Why is it so big?

477
00:33:53,470 --> 00:33:56,766
Don't you know how tiny my mouth is?

478
00:33:56,790 --> 00:33:57,806
Did you add raw garlic?

479
00:33:57,830 --> 00:34:01,200
Of course, I did. You
don't like it any other way.

480
00:34:03,770 --> 00:34:05,836
- Please.
- Aigoo, Jong Hui.

481
00:34:05,860 --> 00:34:07,196
- I'm here!
- Hey.

482
00:34:07,220 --> 00:34:08,536
- Jae Pil's here.
- Oppa, you're here?

483
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:09,706
The pork belly smells amazing.

484
00:34:09,730 --> 00:34:10,956
There are extra utensils there, right?

485
00:34:10,980 --> 00:34:13,336
- Sit down.
- Come here and sit down.

486
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:15,446
- I'm hungry.
- You must be starving.

487
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:17,736
Here you go. I saved some for you.

488
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,490
Thank you!

489
00:34:20,510 --> 00:34:23,286
Let's have a glass
now that Jae Pil is here.

490
00:34:23,310 --> 00:34:24,386
Good work, everyone!

491
00:34:24,410 --> 00:34:25,626
Good work today!

492
00:34:25,650 --> 00:34:28,990
Good work!

493
00:34:36,220 --> 00:34:39,996
So, did you look into it?

494
00:34:40,020 --> 00:34:42,416
What has she been up to lately?

495
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:45,406
Yes. I had someone tail her.

496
00:34:45,430 --> 00:34:48,266
She often goes to a
restaurant in Yeongeun Market.

497
00:34:48,290 --> 00:34:50,416
The market?

498
00:34:50,440 --> 00:34:51,676
Why there?

499
00:34:51,700 --> 00:34:53,166
We found out that

500
00:34:53,190 --> 00:34:56,816
it's run by the mother of a friend
from her bus attendant days.

501
00:34:56,840 --> 00:35:01,210
She meets that friend and
frequents her home, too.

502
00:35:02,270 --> 00:35:04,070
Unbelievable.

503
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:19,956
Dr. Seo In Woo is on call tonight, right?

504
00:35:19,980 --> 00:35:21,776
Not Dr. Han Jae Pil?

505
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,246
I think so.

506
00:35:23,270 --> 00:35:27,866
What if we get slammed with calls again
with that scatterbrained doctor?

507
00:35:27,890 --> 00:35:30,966
It's easier when Dr. Han is on call.

508
00:35:30,990 --> 00:35:33,276
He handles emergencies so well.

509
00:35:33,300 --> 00:35:36,170
Of course. That's my son.

510
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:41,666
But I feel bad for Dr. Han
sometimes, though.

511
00:35:41,690 --> 00:35:44,726
- Why?
- You know.

512
00:35:44,750 --> 00:35:46,926
Patient Han Gi Bok.

513
00:35:46,950 --> 00:35:49,326
Being an intern is tough enough,

514
00:35:49,350 --> 00:35:51,956
but he has to deal with
his difficult father, too.

515
00:35:51,980 --> 00:35:54,746
The man snaps at
everything and always yells.

516
00:35:54,770 --> 00:35:58,046
If I were Dr. Han, gosh,
I don't even want to imagine it.

517
00:35:58,070 --> 00:36:00,066
It must be so embarrassing for him.

518
00:36:00,090 --> 00:36:01,956
He has to be cautious
with the hospital, too.

519
00:36:01,980 --> 00:36:03,326
True.

520
00:36:03,350 --> 00:36:06,676
It's been almost a year since they found
the stroke and readmitted him.

521
00:36:06,700 --> 00:36:08,576
Exactly.

522
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:11,926
The ward tried to push for discharge
because of bed availability,

523
00:36:11,950 --> 00:36:16,406
but Dr. Han said it's unsafe at home
with no one to care for him

524
00:36:16,430 --> 00:36:19,060
and begged to keep him here.

525
00:36:19,980 --> 00:36:24,026
Dr. Han is such a decent guy

526
00:36:24,050 --> 00:36:27,176
but seems he wasn't blessed
in the parent department.

527
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:31,046
That young woman who shuffles
around like this? She's the stepmom.

528
00:36:31,070 --> 00:36:34,410
- Really? No wonder.
- Yeah.

529
00:36:35,620 --> 00:36:37,676
Oh, my! Are you all right?

530
00:36:37,700 --> 00:36:39,916
Are you hurt?

531
00:36:39,940 --> 00:36:42,046
- No, no.
- Please get up.

532
00:36:42,070 --> 00:36:45,430
- I-I'm fine.
- Here.

533
00:37:07,490 --> 00:37:09,726
I'm home!

534
00:37:09,750 --> 00:37:11,970
Mom, I'm home.

535
00:37:13,780 --> 00:37:16,386
What on earth are you up to lately?

536
00:37:16,410 --> 00:37:18,776
- Sorry?
- You come home late all the time.

537
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:20,936
You skip riding practices.

538
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:23,806
When I ask where you've been,
you never give me a clear answer.

539
00:37:23,830 --> 00:37:27,676
And the places you go are
merely Yeongeun Market?

540
00:37:27,700 --> 00:37:30,176
- Yeong Sik's Baekban?
- Mom.

541
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:34,136
Don't you know how I loathe you associating
with the people from your past?

542
00:37:34,160 --> 00:37:36,126
Didn't I tell you that life before
you met me never existed?

543
00:37:36,150 --> 00:37:38,576
To erase it from your memory entirely?

544
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:41,376
- I know. But, Mom-
- You know?

545
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:43,476
And that's how you behave?

546
00:37:43,500 --> 00:37:47,156
Feeding me little lies, hanging around
some shabby market

547
00:37:47,180 --> 00:37:48,906
and mixing with shabby people.

548
00:37:48,930 --> 00:37:51,786
Because I knew you'd react like this!

549
00:37:51,810 --> 00:37:53,266
That's why I couldn't tell you.

550
00:37:53,290 --> 00:37:55,316
It was so obvious you'd be like this.

551
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:58,556
But that place, those people...

552
00:37:58,580 --> 00:38:02,520
They might seem
low-class to you, but to me,

553
00:38:03,460 --> 00:38:07,466
they're precious people I've found again.

554
00:38:07,490 --> 00:38:09,426
What?

555
00:38:09,450 --> 00:38:11,370
Honestly, I'm.

556
00:38:12,570 --> 00:38:15,610
I'm having a hard time, Mom. I'm so lonely.

557
00:38:16,470 --> 00:38:21,096
Your absolute love sometimes feels
so suffocating and overwhelming.

558
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:22,866
If I'm just replacing your
daughter, Seung Yeon.

559
00:38:22,890 --> 00:38:24,696
Shut your mouth!

560
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:26,746
Who are you to bring up that name?

561
00:38:26,770 --> 00:38:29,500
Who are you to bring up my daughter...

562
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:38,810
The hair salon seems a bit quiet today.

563
00:39:39,900 --> 00:39:43,876
The owner and managers all went
to an outside meeting.

564
00:39:43,900 --> 00:39:47,636
They're set on this year's Miss Korea Jin
coming from our salon,

565
00:39:47,660 --> 00:39:50,780
so they've been busy
with external stuff lately.

566
00:39:52,070 --> 00:39:54,986
Why search for a candidate outside

567
00:39:55,010 --> 00:39:57,990
when beautiful Ms. Ko
Yeong Rye is right here?

568
00:39:58,930 --> 00:40:00,446
Oppa!

569
00:40:00,470 --> 00:40:04,136
My hand slipped and almost nicked
a bald spot just now.

570
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:07,386
No joking when I'm holding scissors.

571
00:40:07,410 --> 00:40:10,056
Okay. Sorry.

572
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:12,920
Let's eat after you're done. My treat.

573
00:40:13,910 --> 00:40:17,306
I'm headed to the hospital today.

574
00:40:17,330 --> 00:40:19,610
For Jae Pil's father.

575
00:40:20,900 --> 00:40:22,876
Jae Pil again?

576
00:40:22,900 --> 00:40:25,836
I don't like him these days.

577
00:40:25,860 --> 00:40:28,256
Okay. I'll drive you to the hospital, then.

578
00:40:28,280 --> 00:40:31,586
I-It's fine! I can just take the bus.
It's really fine.

579
00:40:31,610 --> 00:40:33,226
Just say yes. It's on my way.

580
00:40:33,250 --> 00:40:35,620
Looks like it's raining, too.

581
00:40:47,340 --> 00:40:51,060
Geez, what's with the sudden rain?

582
00:40:51,980 --> 00:40:55,476
Yeong Rye is supposed to come today.

583
00:40:55,500 --> 00:40:59,200
I hope she doesn't get drenched
without an umbrella.

584
00:41:23,220 --> 00:41:24,820
Seo Jong Hui?

585
00:41:25,630 --> 00:41:29,500
Hey. Why didn't you buy an umbrella.

586
00:41:29,865 --> 00:41:49,853
Officail Website : kissasian.be

587
00:41:49,877 --> 00:42:09,865
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

588
00:41:31,890 --> 00:41:33,300
You...

589
00:41:37,180 --> 00:41:38,890
Jae Pil.

590
00:42:06,310 --> 00:42:07,910
Wait, wait.

591
00:42:11,460 --> 00:42:13,026
Thanks, Oppa.

592
00:42:13,050 --> 00:42:16,166
Thanks to you, I got
here dry and comfortably.

593
00:42:16,190 --> 00:42:18,080
Here. Take this.

594
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:20,896
I'll use it well and return it.

595
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:22,276
With interest.

596
00:42:22,300 --> 00:42:23,896
Now you've got me curious.

597
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:26,576
What kind of interest, huh?

598
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:29,556
- Go on. I'll head out.
- Okay.

599
00:42:29,580 --> 00:42:32,930
Drive safe, Oppa. I'm going now.

600
00:42:44,520 --> 00:42:47,376
I can't leave like this. Not fair for me.

601
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:49,096
Have a quick coffee with me.

602
00:42:49,120 --> 00:42:52,046
There's a nice cafe nearby.
Just 30 minutes, okay?

603
00:42:52,070 --> 00:42:54,656
C-Coffee, out of nowhere?

604
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:57,026
- Yeah. Just 30 minutes.
- Oh, my.

605
00:42:57,050 --> 00:42:59,490
Get in. Watch your head.

606
00:43:37,300 --> 00:43:39,066
Drink this.

607
00:43:39,090 --> 00:43:41,450
It'll warm you up.

608
00:43:43,540 --> 00:43:45,150
Thanks.

609
00:43:55,500 --> 00:43:57,146
That's better.

610
00:43:57,170 --> 00:43:59,230
I was getting the chills.

611
00:44:00,020 --> 00:44:02,360
How long were you in the rain?

612
00:44:03,120 --> 00:44:05,000
Since when?

613
00:44:06,600 --> 00:44:08,030
I don't know.

614
00:44:08,790 --> 00:44:11,350
I just kept walking and ended up here.

615
00:44:14,650 --> 00:44:17,190
I'm really hopeless, aren't I?

616
00:44:18,750 --> 00:44:22,736
I do what I want, impulsive,

617
00:44:22,760 --> 00:44:25,200
and always giving people a scare.

618
00:44:26,010 --> 00:44:27,976
That's Seo Jong Hui's charm.

619
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:30,070
Nothing new.

620
00:44:35,220 --> 00:44:37,520
You call that consolation?

621
00:44:45,570 --> 00:44:47,940
It's working, though.

622
00:44:49,570 --> 00:44:51,936
You're amazing, Han Jae Pil.

623
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:58,096
♫ That place is always
somewhere I can breathe ♫

624
00:44:58,120 --> 00:45:01,976
♫ Even as you held me while I cried ♫

625
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:09,056
♫ You let me have you, my salvation ♫

626
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:11,380
You know, Jae Pil.

627
00:45:12,860 --> 00:45:14,976
I was born dirt poor.

628
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:17,600
I grew up without my parents' love.

629
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:22,850
So, I thought I'd be so happy
if I became the daughter of a rich family.

630
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:27,580
But I wasn't.

631
00:45:31,340 --> 00:45:34,360
There's no such thing
as a freebie in this world,

632
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:39,690
and I'm only realizing
that too late. So foolish.

633
00:45:41,410 --> 00:45:46,860
♫ I once existed in this world ♫

634
00:45:47,850 --> 00:45:53,720
♫ Back to that place again ♫

635
00:45:57,850 --> 00:45:59,590
I've.

636
00:46:03,580 --> 00:46:05,210
I've

637
00:46:06,940 --> 00:46:09,760
always been envious of Yeong Rye.

638
00:46:13,150 --> 00:46:15,320
Back then,

639
00:46:18,390 --> 00:46:20,720
and even now.

640
00:46:23,750 --> 00:46:27,136
Her family and friends who cherish her.

641
00:46:27,160 --> 00:46:30,360
When I see her smiling among them,

642
00:46:35,680 --> 00:46:37,360
she's beautiful.

643
00:46:39,960 --> 00:46:44,370
She shines so much that
I wish I were her sometimes.

644
00:46:56,130 --> 00:46:57,680
You're right.

645
00:46:58,990 --> 00:47:01,390
Yeong Rye really does shine.

646
00:47:03,030 --> 00:47:05,976
She's smart and considerate,

647
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:10,686
and she's even picked
up a bit of humor lately.

648
00:47:10,710 --> 00:47:13,636
She's gotten fun, too.

649
00:47:13,660 --> 00:47:15,300
But

650
00:47:16,900 --> 00:47:20,500
everyone has their own kind of sparkle.

651
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:24,880
They're just different from each other.

652
00:47:28,650 --> 00:47:31,900
I hope you find your sparkle again.

653
00:47:34,060 --> 00:47:35,940
Like you used to.

654
00:47:37,730 --> 00:47:39,940
Like I used to?

655
00:47:49,070 --> 00:47:51,506
Do you think I can?

656
00:47:51,530 --> 00:47:53,366
Sure, you can.

657
00:47:53,390 --> 00:47:55,320
You're you.

658
00:47:57,460 --> 00:48:00,220
We should put some ointment on that cut.

659
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:07,840
♫ The place I will return to ♫

660
00:48:09,670 --> 00:48:16,670
♫ You, to whom I will return to ♫

661
00:48:39,390 --> 00:48:41,596
Yeong Rye.

662
00:48:41,620 --> 00:48:43,480
Yes, Ahjussi.

663
00:48:44,530 --> 00:48:46,080
I

664
00:48:47,310 --> 00:48:51,776
Tend to make people uncomfortable, don't I?

665
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:56,200
I'm fussy, and I shout
at the slightest thing.

666
00:48:59,450 --> 00:49:02,360
Why are you saying that?

667
00:49:03,250 --> 00:49:05,046
Did someone say something?

668
00:49:05,070 --> 00:49:08,350
No, it's just

669
00:49:10,040 --> 00:49:14,370
getting old makes you think.

670
00:49:15,730 --> 00:49:19,656
I've got such a fiery temper.

671
00:49:19,680 --> 00:49:25,176
I'm sure Jae Pil must worry.

672
00:49:25,200 --> 00:49:30,976
And here I am, camped out at his workplace.

673
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:33,466
It's not like that, Ahjussi.

674
00:49:33,490 --> 00:49:35,866
Being close by puts his mind at ease.

675
00:49:35,890 --> 00:49:37,946
From Jae Pil's point of view.

676
00:49:37,970 --> 00:49:45,356
He's just doing his duty as a son,
even if he resents me.

677
00:49:45,380 --> 00:49:50,656
I'm sure he's self-conscious around here.

678
00:49:50,680 --> 00:49:52,720
Right?

679
00:49:54,360 --> 00:49:56,596
Not at all.

680
00:49:56,620 --> 00:49:59,556
You know I'm really
close to Jae Pil, right?

681
00:49:59,580 --> 00:50:03,696
He's never said anything
even remotely like that.

682
00:50:03,720 --> 00:50:06,916
I swear on my mom's cooking.

683
00:50:06,940 --> 00:50:10,480
Aigoo. That's quite the serious stake.

684
00:50:14,230 --> 00:50:18,750
But that punk hasn't dropped by today.

685
00:50:23,490 --> 00:50:25,106
You're right.

686
00:50:25,130 --> 00:50:27,730
Maybe he's not done with work yet.

687
00:50:40,550 --> 00:50:43,496
Okay. That's enough.

688
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:45,790
You're so meticulous.

689
00:50:47,800 --> 00:50:51,006
Apply it one more time before bed.
I'll give you some ointment.

690
00:50:51,030 --> 00:50:52,300
Okay.

691
00:50:55,420 --> 00:50:57,050
Jong Hui.

692
00:50:58,050 --> 00:50:59,766
Yeong Rye!

693
00:50:59,790 --> 00:51:02,476
Why... Why are you drenched?

694
00:51:02,500 --> 00:51:04,366
Were you caught in the rain?

695
00:51:04,390 --> 00:51:06,856
And what's that cut on your cheek?

696
00:51:06,880 --> 00:51:09,666
You know I'm a bit odd.

697
00:51:09,690 --> 00:51:13,676
For some reason, I
wanted to feel the rain today.

698
00:51:13,700 --> 00:51:19,346
Gosh, I already got an earful
from this doctor here,

699
00:51:19,370 --> 00:51:22,776
so cut me some slack, please?

700
00:51:22,800 --> 00:51:26,326
You should've bought a cheap
umbrella or something.

701
00:51:26,350 --> 00:51:28,350
Your hair is all wet.

702
00:51:29,290 --> 00:51:31,370
You'll catch a cold.

703
00:51:38,320 --> 00:51:41,446
I was just about to go check on him.

704
00:51:41,470 --> 00:51:43,176
You're done with his haircut?

705
00:51:43,200 --> 00:51:44,686
Yeah.

706
00:51:44,710 --> 00:51:49,626
But he doesn't seem to
be in great shape today.

707
00:51:49,650 --> 00:51:51,346
Yeah?

708
00:51:51,370 --> 00:51:54,296
How come? He usually
perks up when he sees you.

709
00:51:54,320 --> 00:51:57,860
I'm not sure. Make sure to swing by later.

710
00:52:03,020 --> 00:52:05,556
Go home and take a hot shower, okay?

711
00:52:05,580 --> 00:52:07,826
All right.

712
00:52:07,850 --> 00:52:11,400
You've gotten so naggy, Ko Yeong Rye.

713
00:52:14,530 --> 00:52:16,600
Thanks for today.

714
00:52:18,380 --> 00:52:19,686
I'm going.

715
00:52:19,710 --> 00:52:21,500
Get home safe.

716
00:52:32,620 --> 00:52:34,766
Let's go. I'll walk you to the bus stop.

717
00:52:34,790 --> 00:52:36,516
It's okay. There's no need.

718
00:52:36,540 --> 00:52:39,806
If you've got time, go
check on your dad. I'm off.

719
00:52:39,830 --> 00:52:41,346
It's his bedtime.

720
00:52:41,370 --> 00:52:42,926
I said I'm fine.

721
00:52:42,950 --> 00:52:44,666
Make sure to see your dad, okay?

722
00:52:44,690 --> 00:52:47,390
I'm going. Bye!

723
00:52:50,150 --> 00:52:52,776
Get home safe!

724
00:52:52,800 --> 00:52:55,050
Thanks for today, once again.

725
00:53:13,950 --> 00:53:16,376
Okay. That's enough.

726
00:53:16,400 --> 00:53:20,000
Apply it one more time before bed.
I'll give you some ointment.

727
00:54:38,580 --> 00:54:40,560
I'm sorry, Mom.

728
00:54:41,560 --> 00:54:44,470
I got too worked up earlier.

729
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:48,406
I won't do that again.

730
00:54:48,430 --> 00:54:49,910
All right.

731
00:54:50,970 --> 00:54:54,156
I got too emotional earlier, too.

732
00:54:54,180 --> 00:54:56,876
Is your cut okay?

733
00:54:56,900 --> 00:54:58,840
Yes, it's fine.

734
00:55:00,370 --> 00:55:02,670
I'm going to head upstairs.

735
00:55:06,430 --> 00:55:08,060
Jong Hui.

736
00:55:14,150 --> 00:55:17,070
You know I love you very much, right?

737
00:55:18,070 --> 00:55:20,950
I can't live without you now.

738
00:55:21,950 --> 00:55:23,710
I know.

739
00:55:26,190 --> 00:55:28,080
Good night, Mom.

740
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:10,380
Hey. Why didn't you buy an umbrella.

741
00:56:13,300 --> 00:56:16,296
Everyone has their own kind of sparkle.

742
00:56:16,320 --> 00:56:19,206
They're just different from each other.

743
00:56:19,230 --> 00:56:22,390
I hope you find your sparkle again.

744
00:56:24,610 --> 00:56:26,360
Like you used to.

745
00:57:55,470 --> 00:57:57,276
This is "Awake in the Night."

746
00:57:57,300 --> 00:57:59,606
Here's our next story.

747
00:57:59,630 --> 00:58:02,326
There are many stories about crushes today.

748
00:58:02,350 --> 00:58:06,406
This story was sent by Dong Won
from Injeong-dong.

749
00:58:06,430 --> 00:58:09,706
On the quiet campus path
where I first walked with her,

750
00:58:09,730 --> 00:58:11,596
this song was playing.

751
00:58:11,620 --> 00:58:14,396
Did her heart flutter just like mine?

752
00:58:14,420 --> 00:58:16,896
"Now I want to be brave, take her hand,

753
00:58:16,920 --> 00:58:19,876
and listen to this song together."

754
00:58:19,900 --> 00:58:23,886
He has requested Cho
Deok Bae's "My Old Story."

755
00:58:23,910 --> 00:58:26,176
Let's listen together.

756
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:29,686
♫ Do you remember ♫
[Giant, 10th Anniversary, 05.21.1982]

757
00:58:29,710 --> 00:58:33,276
♫ that lonely little alley? ♫

758
00:58:33,300 --> 00:58:39,956
♫ I still remember it, even now ♫

759
00:58:39,980 --> 00:58:47,116
♫ Couldn't say "I love you,"
aching through those days ♫

760
00:58:47,140 --> 00:58:54,016
♫ Did you know? ♫

761
00:58:54,040 --> 00:58:58,296
♫ Those lovely nights
of my careless younger years ♫

762
00:58:58,320 --> 00:59:01,230
[Yeonseo University Hospital]

763
00:59:04,320 --> 00:59:05,976
Father, what are you doing?

764
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:09,526
Can't you see? I'm going home.

765
00:59:09,550 --> 00:59:11,166
Father, why are you suddenly.

766
00:59:11,190 --> 00:59:12,696
Be quiet!

767
00:59:12,720 --> 00:59:16,786
I can't stay here another
minute. I'm suffocating.

768
00:59:16,810 --> 00:59:18,826
I hate being crammed into a ward

769
00:59:18,850 --> 00:59:21,356
like a chicken coop with strangers.

770
00:59:21,380 --> 00:59:23,896
I'm sick of hospital food that
tastes like nothing.

771
00:59:23,920 --> 00:59:27,476
And this rehab or whatever
doesn't seem to help anyway.

772
00:59:27,500 --> 00:59:29,656
I'll go home for outpatient
care or whatever.

773
00:59:29,680 --> 00:59:31,666
Father, you can't be discharged yet.

774
00:59:31,690 --> 00:59:34,620
You still need medication,

775
00:59:36,510 --> 00:59:40,396
and if you leave now, you could
have a cerebral hemorrhage again.

776
00:59:40,420 --> 00:59:42,276
It's my body, not yours.

777
00:59:42,300 --> 00:59:44,616
I know it better than you.

778
00:59:44,640 --> 00:59:47,886
That blocked vessel
feels more or less cleared.

779
00:59:47,910 --> 00:59:52,286
And if I just take my medication,
it's the same here or at home.

780
00:59:52,310 --> 00:59:54,386
It's been ages.

781
00:59:54,410 --> 00:59:56,726
This damn hospital is all about business.

782
00:59:56,750 --> 01:00:00,950
Locking people up until they get depressed.

783
01:00:04,600 --> 01:00:05,626
All right.

784
01:00:05,650 --> 01:00:08,140
Let go! Get your hands off!

785
01:00:24,090 --> 01:00:26,916
Gosh, it pisses me off
the more I think about it.

786
01:00:26,940 --> 01:00:28,256
If he's her boyfriend, fine.

787
01:00:28,280 --> 01:00:32,640
How dare that scrawny punk
show up acting all cocky?

788
01:00:34,580 --> 01:00:36,156
I wouldn't say it if he's the kid's dad.

789
01:00:36,180 --> 01:00:39,200
His big eyes are all he's got.

790
01:00:43,280 --> 01:00:46,936
So what? It's not like you can't score
just because there's a goalkeeper.

791
01:00:46,960 --> 01:00:49,316
Does a batter stop hitting just
because there are outfielders?

792
01:00:49,340 --> 01:00:52,450
I'm freaking Kim Jeong Sik!

793
01:00:53,220 --> 01:00:54,620
What?

794
01:00:55,710 --> 01:00:57,930
That little punk.

795
01:00:59,340 --> 01:01:01,706
I'm heading to the salon, not school.

796
01:01:01,730 --> 01:01:04,180
Would that be Jullee Beauty Salon?

797
01:01:05,720 --> 01:01:07,686
Okay.

798
01:01:07,710 --> 01:01:11,010
To Jullee we go.

799
01:01:15,470 --> 01:01:20,876
You must be glad to be reunited
with your friend, Ko Yeong Rye.

800
01:01:20,900 --> 01:01:24,966
Looking back, it was kind of fun back then.

801
01:01:24,990 --> 01:01:29,636
Even if that manager
was a real pain in the neck.

802
01:01:29,660 --> 01:01:34,166
Oh, right. Did you hear about the mess
after you left Cheongah Transportation?

803
01:01:34,190 --> 01:01:37,926
That manager got into a big accident.

804
01:01:37,950 --> 01:01:40,186
We all thought he was going to die.

805
01:01:40,210 --> 01:01:43,456
But, gosh.

806
01:01:43,480 --> 01:01:45,896
He's destined for a long life.

807
01:01:45,920 --> 01:01:48,416
Maybe because he gets cursed at so much.

808
01:01:48,440 --> 01:01:51,436
I also switched my job right after,
so I heard later.

809
01:01:51,460 --> 01:01:55,356
But because of the aftereffects,
he eventually got fired.

810
01:01:55,380 --> 01:01:57,116
Went to another place but got canned again.

811
01:01:57,140 --> 01:01:59,126
In the end, he just vanished.

812
01:01:59,150 --> 01:02:01,570
I'm not really interested.

813
01:02:02,570 --> 01:02:04,186
Let's drive quietly.

814
01:02:04,210 --> 01:02:06,366
Okay. I'm sorry.

815
01:02:06,390 --> 01:02:08,600
I guess you like it quiet.

816
01:02:22,090 --> 01:02:24,466
All right. Let's speed it up!

817
01:02:24,490 --> 01:02:28,256
And clean that up already!
So freaking annoying.

818
01:02:28,280 --> 01:02:30,870
Hey, come on! Speed it up!

819
01:02:39,360 --> 01:02:41,176
Hey!

820
01:02:41,200 --> 01:02:44,966
We're busy as hell. What are you doing?
Are you here to play?

821
01:02:44,990 --> 01:02:47,316
Stop slacking off and get to work!

822
01:02:47,340 --> 01:02:48,696
So freaking annoying.

823
01:02:48,720 --> 01:02:51,036
Do you all want to stay late?

824
01:02:51,060 --> 01:02:52,850
Hurry up!

825
01:04:55,400 --> 01:04:57,400
You bitch.

826
01:04:58,620 --> 01:05:00,180
You're smiling?

827
01:05:01,690 --> 01:05:05,600
After shoving my life
into the gutter like this?

828
01:05:19,100 --> 01:05:21,956
Welcome to Jullee Beauty Salon.

829
01:05:21,980 --> 01:05:24,456
Oh, my! Oh, my.

830
01:05:24,480 --> 01:05:26,916
Jong Hui, what brings you here
without an appointment?

831
01:05:26,940 --> 01:05:29,536
Something came up,

832
01:05:29,560 --> 01:05:32,086
so I came to ask for an urgent favor.

833
01:05:32,110 --> 01:05:33,536
To me?

834
01:05:33,560 --> 01:05:35,476
Is it possible?

835
01:05:35,500 --> 01:05:37,600
Well, what kind of...

836
01:05:46,600 --> 01:05:48,306
Where are we going?

837
01:05:48,330 --> 01:05:50,626
You said you needed an on-site
hairstylist for an event.

838
01:05:50,650 --> 01:05:52,776
That was obviously a lie.

839
01:05:52,800 --> 01:05:54,996
I want to go somewhere with you.

840
01:05:55,020 --> 01:05:57,330
Oh, hurry up!

841
01:06:27,920 --> 01:06:31,786
Wait. What's this all of a sudden?

842
01:06:31,810 --> 01:06:33,566
You were discharged?

843
01:06:33,590 --> 01:06:35,026
Jae Pil!

844
01:06:35,050 --> 01:06:36,236
- You came.
- Yeah.

845
01:06:36,260 --> 01:06:38,326
I stopped by between appointments

846
01:06:38,350 --> 01:06:40,346
and they said he'd been discharged.

847
01:06:40,370 --> 01:06:42,376
Out of the blue, like a bolt from the blue.

848
01:06:42,400 --> 01:06:46,086
And the bus took forever as I was coming.

849
01:06:46,110 --> 01:06:50,196
I almost slipped back into
old habits and grabbed a taxi,

850
01:06:50,220 --> 01:06:54,946
but to pay for that, I'd have to sell
a bunch more lotions door-to-door.

851
01:06:54,970 --> 01:06:57,896
Anyway, that's not the point.

852
01:06:57,920 --> 01:06:59,976
Are you sure he can be discharged?

853
01:07:00,000 --> 01:07:01,576
No.

854
01:07:01,600 --> 01:07:03,806
Dad just dug in his heels.

855
01:07:03,830 --> 01:07:06,676
I... I'm not staying in
the hospital anymore.

856
01:07:06,700 --> 01:07:09,986
I'll do outpatient and
take my meds at home.

857
01:07:10,010 --> 01:07:13,616
But when Se Ri is at
school, and I'm at work,

858
01:07:13,640 --> 01:07:16,826
no one is home. How are
you going to manage alone?

859
01:07:16,850 --> 01:07:19,516
Even today, I've got massage
appointments lined up.

860
01:07:19,540 --> 01:07:21,406
I've got to head out right away.

861
01:07:21,430 --> 01:07:24,796
Do you think I'm a child
who can't be left alone?

862
01:07:24,820 --> 01:07:27,296
Stop treating me like some fool.

863
01:07:27,320 --> 01:07:30,056
You're not a child, but you are a patient.

864
01:07:30,080 --> 01:07:33,146
Please stop with your
unreasonable stubbornness.

865
01:07:33,170 --> 01:07:35,380
Every time you do this,

866
01:07:36,380 --> 01:07:38,016
we're at our wits' end.

867
01:07:38,040 --> 01:07:39,656
W-What did I do, huh?

868
01:07:39,680 --> 01:07:42,476
How have I been torturing you two? Huh?

869
01:07:42,500 --> 01:07:46,936
Okay. Okay, fine. Let's at least
take your meds first.

870
01:07:46,960 --> 01:07:49,396
You haven't had your lunch dose yet, right?

871
01:07:49,420 --> 01:07:51,266
Leave it. I'll take it myself.

872
01:07:51,290 --> 01:07:53,886
Why go through the trouble?
Take it while we're here.

873
01:07:53,910 --> 01:07:55,706
I have to head back out.

874
01:07:55,730 --> 01:07:59,876
I-I said I'll take them!
Why make such a fuss!

875
01:07:59,900 --> 01:08:02,280
Father, please!

876
01:08:03,100 --> 01:08:06,046
Please, get a grip already!

877
01:08:06,070 --> 01:08:08,066
Have you ever thought about

878
01:08:08,090 --> 01:08:11,426
how your overbearing ways have hurt us?

879
01:08:11,450 --> 01:08:15,216
Why do you think I learned boxing?

880
01:08:15,240 --> 01:08:18,246
To be so much stronger than you,
so I could beat you.

881
01:08:18,270 --> 01:08:20,836
Because!

882
01:08:20,860 --> 01:08:24,116
Because I was weaker than you,

883
01:08:24,140 --> 01:08:26,520
and in the end, Mom...

884
01:08:36,630 --> 01:08:39,126
What? Dad, you got discharged?

885
01:08:39,150 --> 01:08:42,516
Hey, Se Ri, you're home?

886
01:08:42,540 --> 01:08:44,756
You're home?

887
01:08:44,780 --> 01:08:50,106
Wow. The whole family together
after so long is awkward, but kind of nice.

888
01:08:50,130 --> 01:08:51,706
Right, Oppa?

889
01:08:51,730 --> 01:08:53,740
Right, Dad?

890
01:09:14,930 --> 01:09:16,576
Is this it?

891
01:09:16,600 --> 01:09:19,666
The place you wanted to come with me?

892
01:09:19,690 --> 01:09:21,166
Yeah.

893
01:09:21,190 --> 01:09:23,720
I really wanted to come at least once.

894
01:09:24,720 --> 01:09:29,860
Wow. It's been seven
years, and nothing's changed.

895
01:09:30,930 --> 01:09:33,110
That's amazing.

896
01:09:37,440 --> 01:09:39,920
Dating!

897
01:09:40,770 --> 01:09:42,446
Hey, your face got really red!

898
01:09:42,470 --> 01:09:45,780
She's dating! She's dating!

899
01:09:59,710 --> 01:10:02,360
- That's not it.
- It is!

900
01:10:40,800 --> 01:10:43,450
You started chewing again?

901
01:10:44,870 --> 01:10:47,326
I thought your mom hated that.

902
01:10:47,350 --> 01:10:49,220
Well, sometimes.

903
01:10:50,040 --> 01:10:53,670
I can't live doing only what Mom likes.

904
01:10:56,110 --> 01:10:58,286
When we were going here,

905
01:10:58,310 --> 01:11:00,516
what was so funny all the time?

906
01:11:00,540 --> 01:11:03,500
All I remember is nonstop giggling.

907
01:11:04,800 --> 01:11:07,026
We were young back then.

908
01:11:07,050 --> 01:11:11,290
Watching a fallen leaf
roll by was funny to us.

909
01:11:18,900 --> 01:11:21,470
For the past seven years,

910
01:11:22,440 --> 01:11:25,426
whenever I was lonely,
struggled, or exhausted,

911
01:11:25,450 --> 01:11:28,220
a few images came to mind.

912
01:11:29,770 --> 01:11:32,666
Going to school with you,

913
01:11:32,690 --> 01:11:35,906
eating at your house and playing
with Yeong Bae and Yeong Mi.

914
01:11:35,930 --> 01:11:37,820
And

915
01:11:40,070 --> 01:11:43,320
my memories with Jae Pil.

916
01:11:46,610 --> 01:11:50,960
Without those things, I probably
wouldn't have made it through.

917
01:11:54,190 --> 01:11:59,180
So lately, I'm starting
to feel a little happy again.

918
01:12:00,100 --> 01:12:02,256
Even when things are rough with Mom,

919
01:12:02,280 --> 01:12:05,636
I'm not as lonely as before.

920
01:12:05,660 --> 01:12:09,380
And I feel like I have
some people on my side.

921
01:12:18,330 --> 01:12:20,576
You also remember, right?

922
01:12:20,600 --> 01:12:24,680
Jae Pil gave me these shoes
as a gift a long time ago.

923
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:28,520
I wore them the day I ran away.

924
01:12:29,710 --> 01:12:32,176
Thanks to that, I got
to take these with me.

925
01:12:32,200 --> 01:12:34,990
I couldn't take anything else.

926
01:12:37,010 --> 01:12:41,010
I kept them hidden in a drawer,

927
01:12:46,040 --> 01:12:48,810
but I'm going to wear them again.

928
01:12:53,310 --> 01:12:55,140
Starting today.

929
01:13:03,700 --> 01:13:08,100
I tried not to remember,
but it all came back.

930
01:13:11,250 --> 01:13:14,620
How much I leaned on you,

931
01:13:17,720 --> 01:13:21,530
how much I liked Jae Pil.

932
01:13:26,710 --> 01:13:29,180
He's my first love.

933
01:13:39,300 --> 01:13:41,640
So, Yeong Rye.

934
01:13:43,630 --> 01:13:48,360
I want to start over with Jae Pil.

935
01:13:52,790 --> 01:13:55,180
You'll help me, right?

936
01:14:37,730 --> 01:14:39,420
Me, too.

937
01:14:44,630 --> 01:14:46,410
For me

938
01:14:49,710 --> 01:14:52,160
he's my first love, too.

939
01:14:53,160 --> 01:14:55,040
Jae Pil is.

940
01:14:59,710 --> 01:15:01,370
Really?

941
01:15:02,960 --> 01:15:04,760
Back then,

942
01:15:06,920 --> 01:15:11,810
I felt I shouldn't show it,
so I just watched from behind.

943
01:15:14,110 --> 01:15:17,180
And you're a friend I
love after my family...

944
01:15:18,460 --> 01:15:19,930
No.

945
01:15:21,410 --> 01:15:24,590
You're a friend I love
as much as my family.

946
01:15:25,690 --> 01:15:27,120
But now,

947
01:15:29,460 --> 01:15:32,130
I don't want to hide my feelings.

948
01:15:34,520 --> 01:15:37,306
I want to be honest.

949
01:15:37,330 --> 01:15:39,330
I want to protect it.

950
01:15:41,730 --> 01:15:43,790
So, Jong Hui.

951
01:15:46,090 --> 01:15:47,920
I can't.

952
01:15:50,330 --> 01:15:52,340
I can't help you.

953
01:15:54,590 --> 01:15:56,100
All right.

954
01:16:01,960 --> 01:16:04,100
That's fair.

955
01:16:11,380 --> 01:16:13,220
Okay.

956
01:16:18,110 --> 01:16:20,640
Then, what matters

957
01:16:28,260 --> 01:16:30,900
is Jae Pil's heart, right?

958
01:17:09,540 --> 01:17:15,040
♫ Call my name ♫

959
01:17:16,510 --> 01:17:22,270
♫ Break this silence ♫

960
01:17:24,080 --> 01:17:26,206
Han Jae Pil, pick a lane.

961
01:17:26,230 --> 01:17:30,126
If you hesitate, I'm going to floor it.

962
01:17:30,150 --> 01:17:32,296
You had a pretty girlfriend all this time?

963
01:17:32,320 --> 01:17:33,536
It's not like that, man.

964
01:17:33,560 --> 01:17:35,776
But it's not like I'm not. Am I right?

965
01:17:35,800 --> 01:17:38,036
Jae Pil, you know your other girlfriend?

966
01:17:38,060 --> 01:17:39,106
Who is this lady?

967
01:17:39,130 --> 01:17:41,996
I like this woman.
Although it's one-sided for now.

968
01:17:42,020 --> 01:17:45,136
In every moment that felt unbearable,

969
01:17:45,160 --> 01:17:48,106
she was always

970
01:17:48,130 --> 01:17:50,320
right next to me.
